# Commit messages

When you modify files in this repository (code, docs, config, or rules), end your reply with a **git commit message** the user can paste as-is.

- Use a conventional-style **subject line** (e.g. `feat:`, `fix:`, `docs:`, `chore:`) under ~72 characters when reasonable.
- Add a **body** when the change is non-trivial: what changed, why, and any follow-ups or risks.
- Write in full sentences in the body; keep the subject imperative and concise.
- Put the full message in one fenced `text` block so the user can copy subject and body together.
